          "id": "ai-16",
          "title": "Toto 2.0: Time series forecasting enters the scaling era",
          "link": "https://www.datadoghq.com/blog/ai/toto-2/",
          "image": "https://web-assets.dd-static.net/42588/1778796486-1778691695-toto-2-hero_resized.png",
          "source": "Datadog",
          "tags": [
            "ai",
            "data",
            "machine-learning",
            "opensource"
          ],
          "description": "Datadog's Toto 2.0, a scalable time series forecasting model family, is now available on Hugging Face.",
          "one-liner": "Datadog has released Toto 2.0, an open-weights family of time series forecasting models up to 2.5B parameters on Hugging Face, demonstrating improved performance and scalability without saturation.",
          "summary": {
            "what": "Datadog launched Toto 2.0, a family of open-weights time series forecasting models ranging from 4 million to 2.5 billion parameters, now available on Hugging Face under the Apache 2.0 license. Toto 2.0 sets new state-of-the-art results on benchmarks like BOOM, GIFT-Eval, and TIME, showing monotonic improvement with scale and 7x greater parameter efficiency than Toto 1.0. It features contiguous patch masking (CPM) for faster inference.",
            "why": "Toto 2.0 signifies a significant advancement in time series forecasting, proving that scaling models reliably improves performance in this domain, similar to how it has in NLP and vision. This makes powerful, general-purpose time series foundation models more accessible and practical for a broader range of applications, especially in observability.",
            "takeaway": "Developers working with time series data can experiment with Toto 2.0 models on Hugging Face to improve forecasting accuracy and inference speed for their applications."
          },
          "decoder": "* **Time series forecasting**: The process of predicting future values of a variable based on its past values, often used for data that changes over time, like stock prices, sensor readings, or website traffic.\n* **Open-weights**: Refers to a model where the trained parameters (weights) are publicly released, allowing anyone to download, use, and further develop the model.\n* **Hugging Face**: A popular platform and community for machine learning, providing tools, datasets, and pretrained models, often for natural language processing and computer vision.\n* **CRPS (Continuous Ranked Probability Score)**: A metric used to evaluate the quality of probabilistic forecasts, measuring how well the predicted distribution of outcomes aligns with the actual observed outcomes.\n* **MASE (Mean Absolute Scaled Error)**: A measure of point forecast accuracy, normalized against a naive seasonal baseline, making it suitable for comparing forecasts across different time series.",
          "rating": 5,
          "content-template-path": "full-content/2026-05-15/ai-16"
        }
      ]
