          "id": "tech-13",
          "title": "Bitcoin trader recovers $400,000 using Claude AI after getting 'stoned' and losing wallet password 11 years ago",
          "link": "https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/cryptocurrency/bitcoin-trader-recovers-usd400-000-using-claude-ai-after-losing-wallet-password-11-years-ago-bot-tried-3-5-trillion-passwords-before-decrypting-an-old-wallet-backup",
          "image": "https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/3jd3yz7VBpd9cM9AFR5C8A-2000-80.jpg",
          "source": "Tom's Hardware",
          "tags": [
            "crypto",
            "ai",
            "security",
            "blockchain"
          ],
          "description": "Claude discovered an old backup wallet file that it successfully decrypted.",
          "one-liner": "A Bitcoin trader recovered $400,000 worth of BTC, lost for 11 years, by using Anthropic's Claude AI to find and decrypt an old wallet backup.",
          "summary": {
            "what": "X user cprkrn regained access to 5 BTC (worth nearly $400,000) that they had lost for 11 years after changing the password while impaired. Claude AI analyzed their college computer files, found an old wallet backup from December 2019, and identified a bug in the btcrecover tool's password configuration, allowing it to decrypt the private keys.",
            "why": "This incident showcases AI's potential as an advanced analytical tool for complex data recovery and problem-solving, demonstrating its capability to identify subtle logical errors and hidden information within vast, unstructured datasets, moving beyond simple brute-force attacks.",
            "takeaway": "If you have lost cryptocurrency wallets, consider exploring AI tools for complex data analysis to uncover overlooked details or configuration issues in addition to traditional recovery methods."
          },
          "deep-summary": "* X user cprkrn lost access to 5 Bitcoin, currently valued at almost $400,000, 11 years ago after changing the wallet password while impaired.\n* They had been trying to recover the wallet using the open-source tool `btcrecover` without success.\n* After finding an old mnemonic seed phrase that confirmed the wallet's identity, cprkrn dumped their entire college computer files into Anthropic's Claude AI.\n* Claude successfully identified an older wallet backup file from December 2019.\n* Crucially, Claude discovered a bug in how `btcrecover` was combining shared keys and passwords, which was preventing previous recovery attempts.\n* Once this configuration issue was resolved, Claude was able to decrypt the private keys using `btcrecover`, allowing the user to transfer the BTC.\n* This highlights AI's capability to find hidden files and diagnose subtle software configuration problems within large, unstructured datasets.",
          "decoder": "* **Mnemonic seed phrase**: A list of words that stores all the information needed to recover a cryptocurrency wallet.\n* **HD key tree (Hierarchical Deterministic key tree)**: A system where a single seed phrase can generate a tree of keys for multiple cryptocurrency addresses.\n* **btcrecover**: An open-source tool used for recovering lost Bitcoin wallet passwords.",
          "rating": 4,
          "content-template-path": "full-content/2026-05-15/tech-13"
        },
