          "id": "tech-14",
          "title": "OpenAI x Microsoft",
          "link": "https://www.techemails.com/p/openai-x-microsoft",
          "image": "https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!Kgd5!,w_1200,h_675,c_fill,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F79fc15fc-6ea8-4426-acad-117e6c349ba0_922x876.png",
          "source": "Tech Emails",
          "tags": [
            "ai",
            "startup",
            "policy",
            "enterprise"
          ],
          "description": "This post contains emails and messages from and between Satya Nadella, Sam Altman, and Elon Musk regarding OpenAI's relationship to Microsoft.",
          "one-liner": "Leaked emails from the Musk v. Altman lawsuit reveal Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella's aggressive strategy to control OpenAI's IP and internal structures while Sam Altman navigated the November 2023 board crisis.",
          "summary": {
            "what": "Internal emails and messages from the Musk v. Altman (2026) lawsuit expose Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella's July 2022 desire to \"own – the silicon, infra, foundational model IP and 'know how'\" of OpenAI, citing a projected $4 billion P&amp;L loss. The messages also detail Sam Altman's November 2023 communications with Nadella and Kevin Scott during his ousting, discussing potential board members like Diane Greene (whom Nadella strongly opposed) and a proposed board structure with Larry Summers and Bret Taylor.",
            "why": "These leaks illustrate the intense strategic tension and power dynamics inherent in the Microsoft-OpenAI partnership, highlighting Microsoft's desire for deeper control and IP ownership despite being a major investor, especially as OpenAI navigates internal leadership crises and aims for AGI."
          },
          "deep-summary": "* A July 2022 email from Satya Nadella to Microsoft executives expresses concern about Microsoft's financial exposure to OpenAI, projecting a $4 billion P&amp;L loss the following year.\n* Nadella stated his goal was for Microsoft to \"own – the silicon, infra, foundational model IP and 'know how'\" to gain control of its destiny, rather than being \"a very thin layer on top of NVIDIA and all the IP is with Open AI.\"\n* He proposed funding OpenAI's hardware and operational expenses in return for full IP rights and embedding Microsoft staff across OpenAI's stack to ensure self-sufficiency.\n* Texts from November 2023 show Sam Altman communicating with Nadella and Kevin Scott during the period he was removed from OpenAI's board.\n* Altman discussed potential board configurations, including a 5-member board and a smaller board of Bret Taylor, Larry Summers, Adam D'Angelo, and himself as CEO.\n* Nadella and Scott explicitly rejected Diane Greene and Bing Gordon as potential board members due to conflicts with Microsoft's cloud business, with Nadella giving a \"Strong strong no\" for Greene.\n* An October 2020 text from Sam Altman to Elon Musk defends the Microsoft partnership as the best way to secure \"many billions of dollars\" needed to compete with DeepMind while retaining autonomy.\n* Elon Musk criticized the partnership on Twitter in September 2020, stating \"OpenAI is essentially captured by Microsoft.\"\n* Microsoft's board investment memos from 2019 to 2024 were also included in the leak.",
          "decoder": "* **P&amp;L (Profit &amp; Loss)**: A financial statement summarizing revenues, costs, and expenses incurred during a specific period.\n* **AGI (Artificial General Intelligence)**: Hypothetical AI that can understand, learn, and apply intelligence to a wide range of problems, similar to human intelligence.\n* **P&amp;L review**: A business meeting to review the profit and loss statement and discuss financial performance.",
          "rating": 5,
          "content-template-path": "full-content/2026-05-15/tech-14"
        }
      ]
    },
