          "id": "design-13",
          "title": "The death of the empty state in AI products",
          "link": "https://uxdesign.cc/the-death-of-the-empty-state-in-ai-products-2026-e11439fbb688",
          "description": "Many modern AI products rely on a blank prompt box as their main onboarding experience, replacing decades of UX practices that traditionally helped users understand what a product could do and how to start using it effectively. This approach often increases first-session drop-off because users are asked to invent prompts and workflows before they have any context, forcing them to think harder instead of guiding them toward quick success. A better AI onboarding experience would use worked examples, clear starting actions, visible limitations, and interactive guidance that helps users achieve something useful before needing to master prompting."
        },
